From Subject Re Necessity of fuel injector cleaning by dealership In article Jim Grey writes In article writes In your experience how true is it that a fuel injector cleaning will do much more good than just using detergent While I A fuel injector cleaning at the dealer is probably little more than them opening your gas tank dumping in a bottle of fuel injector cleaner and sending you on your merry way Go to KMart and buy the cleaner yourself for This should not be the case if they are at all Fuel injector cleaning is done properly with a can of injector cleaner solvent which is hooked up to the fuel system under high The car is actually run on the solvent during the cleaning The equipment to properly do this is pricey and generally not something the average home mechanic The solvent itself is not very expensive and you could probably make up a hose to fit your system and do it yourself but I didn't tell you Not many in tank cleaners are worth wasting your money There has been a discussion of these products on here from time to time and Chevron Techron not Pro Gard with Techron is generally regarded as the It is however a bit more than a IMHO it will not substitute for proper injector cleaning if they are really crudded You'll have to decide if the price is a better deal than spending your time and or buying equipment to do Scott Keller The Agricultural Group of Monsanto Company packet